{"build_type":"executable","description":"LLM reader op.read (by-symbol) with envelope. argv[1]=function name, stdin=IPM package. Emits {package, payload, map, confidence, omitted}: payload=the requested function's full definition (the answer); map=bodyless skeleton of ALL functions (names-only navigation, separate register, anti-distractor); confidence=exact-symbol-match|not-found (calibrates the reader's trust, anti over-abstention); omitted={functions_total, bodies_shown} (explicit completeness manifest, anti-AbsenceBench). Not-found → no payload, confidence=not-found, error+requested, but map still lists what EXISTS. Guards bad input without crashing (§7). Reuses json-tree-node, read_all_of_stdin, the stdout emitter, summarize_function_members_into_skeleton.","module_name":"retrieve-named-function-bearing-skeleton-dictionary","package_name":"retrieve-named-function-bearing-skeleton-dictionary","function_definitions":{"retrieve-named-function-bearing-skeleton-dictionary":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_fd","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"function_definitions"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_pkgname","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"package_name"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_package","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"package"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_map","variable_type":"str"